  • Method Details

    • put

      boolean put​(K key, V value)
      Ensures the passed key and value to be contained as an entry in the map. Return value indicates new entry.
      Parameters:
      key - the key
      value - the value
      Returns:
      true if an entry was created

    • valuePut

      boolean valuePut​(K sampleKey, V value)
      Ensures the passed value to be either set to an existing entry appropriate to sampleKey or inserted as a new one. Return value indicates new entry.
      Parameters:
      sampleKey - the key
      value - the value
      Returns:
      true if an entry was created
